🛠 Task 1 – Update Package List

Ubuntu

sudo apt update

Upgrade installed packages

sudo apt upgrade -y

Full upgrade

sudo apt full-upgrade -y
🛠 Task 2 – Search Packages
apt search nginx

Package details

apt show nginx

Installed?

dpkg -l | grep nginx
🛠 Task 3 – Install Packages

Example

sudo apt install nginx -y

Install multiple

sudo apt install git curl wget vim -y
🛠 Task 4 – Remove Packages

Remove only

sudo apt remove nginx

Remove completely

sudo apt purge nginx

Cleanup

sudo apt autoremove
🛠 Task 5 – DPKG

Install manually

sudo dpkg -i package.deb

List packages

dpkg -l

Verify package

dpkg -s nginx

List files

dpkg -L nginx
🛠 Task 6 – Repository Management

Repository list

cat /etc/apt/sources.list

Additional repositories

ls /etc/apt/sources.list.d/

Update after changes

sudo apt update
🛠 Task 7 – Snap

Install

sudo snap install code --classic

List snaps

snap list

Remove

sudo snap remove code
🛠 Task 8 – Package Verification

Check broken packages

sudo apt --fix-broken install

Dependencies

apt depends nginx

Reverse dependencies

apt rdepends nginx
🛠 Task 9 – Version Management

Available versions

apt policy nginx

Hold package

sudo apt-mark hold nginx

Unhold

sudo apt-mark unhold nginx
🛠 Task 10 – Package Cleanup

Clear cache

sudo apt clean

Remove old cache

sudo apt autoclean
